<p>Two Eamcs tweaks I forgot about (most of you will know these):</p>
<p>Use Consult&rsquo;s <code>recentf</code> to see a list of files that were edited recently:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4"><code class="language-lisp" data-lang="lisp">  (global-set-key (kbd <span style="color:#e6db74">&#34;C-x C-r&#34;</span>) <span style="color:#e6db74">&#39;consult-recent-file</span>)
</code></pre></div><p>Consult&rsquo;s org-agenda (jump to heading) is quicker than what I usually do, which is to list all ACTIVE keywords in emacs (this is how I list my projects), and then go down the tree to find the specific TODO header I want.</p>
<p>Since I often know what I&rsquo;m looking for within active projects, I can use <code>consult-org-agenda</code>, which narrows headers dynamically as I search. Much faster and clutter-free:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4"><code class="language-lisp" data-lang="lisp">  (global-set-key (kbd <span style="color:#e6db74">&#34;C-c C-h&#34;</span>) <span style="color:#e6db74">&#39;consult-org-agenda</span>)
</code></pre></div>